latestPosts.caption:
I’ve been keeping all the behind-the-scenes deets of @faebeautyofficial under wraps for too long. More than the glossy posts, there’s midnight breakthroughs, happy tears, pinch me moments, and rock bottom ones too that got us here. I am so thrilled to finally share the story of how the FAE dream came to life 💫

Tell me what else you’d like to know and see!

Our first ever Elle Beauty Award - we’ve waited for the day that we’d get recognized for all the work we do to innovate our formulations - so today is a true testament to the fact that sticking to our guns and being innovative, sometimes even at the cost of much longer launch times is always WORTH IT 🙌🏿 🙌🏿 apart from the award - we’d never be here without all the love our community has shown to Lip Whip, Peptide Glaws Gloss and Re:Define - so a big big thank you to everyone whose supported and trusted FAE with their make up purchases over the years 🥹 💕 

Thank You!! @elleindia

September Dump - one of the the hardest, busiest, yet one of the most validating + fulfilling months at FAE

We hosted Fae Day, kickstarted our offline journey with @experiencebroadway_ in gurgaon, launched hydra milk, shot two UNREAL campaigns, prepped for a very special Diwali launch and much much more. 

[fae beauty, entrepreneur, founder, D2c, beauty brand, day in the life, bombay]

@faebeautyofficial turned 5 this week! Some of my core memories from this journey 
1: @pri_ism made some magic with our debut Buildable Matte Lipstick installations 
2: the first FAE offline event - pre COVID, 5 years ago this month - an incredible launch party 
3: the first time we sent out PR - @krishk18 @urshaynesss and I packed and labeled all of these ourselves 
4 & 5: our first two photoshoots
6: the first time we crossed 250 website orders in a day. The first time we felt like our office was getting a bit too small 
7: me and our oldest FAE team member
8 & 9: BTS from our most creative photoshoot 
10 & 11: snippets from our labs/factories - where the magic happens 
12: our team got bigger - and even more since this photo!
13: how I’m feeling about continuing to build FAE over the next 5, 10,15 years 🥂🚀

Just one of the realities of growing a D2c business in today’s competitive environment. If you are a founder or a consumer who has some thoughts on this, leave me a comment below 👇🏾 

Thanks to @samriddh for shedding light on this!

[d2c truths, entrepreneurship, beauty entrepreneur, business ]

Come BTS with me as we shoot our yummiest product campaign yet. Shoot days are the days that I love the most - they’re the days on which I get to take a break from the numbers and staring at my screen all day to work with some of the most creative, skilled, and talented folks in the industry - and I always find myself coming back to work feeling creatively refreshed and inspired ✨

[bts, photoshoot, product photography, D2c business, beauty entrepreneurs ]

Here goes - excited to share my journey building @faebeautyofficial with everyone who might want to know what it’s like to create an authentically Indian beauty brand today. This won’t be a space to glorify the sleepless nights and endless hours of work or sugar coat the tougher days, my goal is to be able to be real, raw and authentic in this space - sharing the not so instagramable moments as much as those worth celebrating, just like we do at Free And Equal Beauty ✨ follow along
